any. Lastly, I'm concerned that fallback handling in Introspector.loadBeanInfo might not catch LinkageError properly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Class loading behavior**\\n\\nI’m examining how Class.forName with the system loader loads SystemLoaderBeanBeanInfo, which extends EmptyBeanInfo. This part seems fine, but I'm noticing there's no descriptor matching for the immediate branch. The fallback with the bean loader failing to load BeanInfo raises a question about why a custom bean loader with a null parent can't load the superclass. It looks like this issue only concerns BeanInfo, not the bean itself, leading to a ClassNotFoundException. It’s good that the context ClassLoader defines BeanInfo clearly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_BHOZN1brEwDubrGFIgKsMcpm|fc_0f4857790a54206c016a0290e3b22081908b6f5f5a429a86d8", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/org.msgpack/msgpack/0.6.10/src/test/java/org_msgpack/msgpack/IntrospectorTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 796, "output": 733, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30201, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778553045739, "responseId": "resp_0f4857790a54206c016a0290d666c081909ef4e9a8260549a1"}}
